# {{APP_NAME}} — AI Assistant Guidelines

This file gives AI coding assistants (Claude, Copilot, etc.) the context needed
to work effectively in this project without asking repetitive orientation questions.

## Project overview

- **Framework:** [PramnosFramework](https://github.com/mrpc/PramnosFramework) v1.2
- **Stack:** PHP 8.4, {{DB_TYPE}}, Docker
- **Namespace:** `{{NAMESPACE}}`
- **CLI entry point:** `./{{CLI_NAME}}` (wraps `bin/{{CLI_NAME}}.php`)

## Running tests

**Always use `./dockertest`, never `vendor/bin/phpunit` directly.**

```bash
./dockertest                         # full suite
./dockertest --filter ClassName      # single test or class
./dockertest --coverage              # HTML coverage report → coverage/
./dockertest --testdox               # human-readable output
```

The script ensures Docker is running, dependencies are installed, and the correct
PHP 8.4 environment is used. Two concurrent `./dockertest` runs will corrupt the
shared test databases — the script enforces a lock and will tell you the PID to
kill if it gets stuck.

## Project structure

```
app/            Application config (app.php, settings.php, keys/)
src/            Application source code
  Controllers/  HTTP controllers (extend Pramnos\Application\Controller)
  Models/       Data models (extend Pramnos\Application\Model or OrmModel)
  Views/        View directories — each view is a folder with view.html.php
  Migrations/   Application migrations (extend Pramnos\Database\Migration)
database/
  migrations/   Migration files (run with ./{{CLI_NAME}} migrate)
  seeds/        Database seeders (run with ./{{CLI_NAME}} db:seed)
tests/
  Unit/         Unit tests (no DB, no network)
  Integration/  Integration tests (real DB via Docker)
www/            Public webroot
bin/            CLI entry point
```

## Key conventions

### Controllers

```php
// Extend Controller — getView() resolves views automatically
class Home extends \Pramnos\Application\Controller
{
    public array $actions = ['display'];

    public function display(array $args = []): void
    {
        $view = $this->getView('Home', 'html');
        $view->assign('title', 'Hello');
        $view->display();
    }
}
```

Views fall back to the framework's bundled scaffold views if no app view exists —
useful during early development.

### Models

```php
// Basic Model — legacy-compatible
class Post extends \Pramnos\Application\Model
{
    public string $table = 'posts';
    public string $primaryKey = 'postid';
}

// OrmModel — modern, with relations/events/casts
class Post extends \Pramnos\Application\OrmModel
{
    public string $table = 'posts';
    protected array $fillable = ['title', 'body', 'author_id'];
    protected array $casts    = ['published_at' => 'datetime'];

    public function author(): \Pramnos\Application\Orm\Relations\BelongsTo
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(User::class, 'author_id', 'userid');
    }
}
```

### QueryBuilder

```php
$db = \Pramnos\Database\Database::getInstance();

$rows = $db->table('posts')
    ->where('status', 'published')
    ->orderBy('created_at', 'desc')
    ->limit(10)
    ->get();
```

### Migrations

```php
class CreatePostsTable extends \Pramnos\Database\Migration
{
    public string $feature = 'app';      // groups migrations
    public int    $priority = 100;       // execution order
    public array  $dependencies = [];    // other migration class names

    public function up(): void
    {
        $schema = $this->application->database->schema();
        if ($schema->hasTable('posts')) return;

        $schema->createTable('posts', function ($table) {
            $table->increments('postid');
            $table->string('title', 255);
            $table->text('body')->nullable();
            $table->integer('created_at');
        });
    }

    public function down(): void
    {
        $this->application->database->schema()->dropTableIfExists('posts');
    }
}
```

Run migrations: `./{{CLI_NAME}} migrate`
Check status: `./{{CLI_NAME}} migrate:status`

### Routing

Routes are defined in `app/routes.php` (or registered via a ServiceProvider):

```php
$router = \Pramnos\Http\Router::getInstance();
$router->get('/posts',       'Posts@index');
$router->post('/posts',      'Posts@store');
$router->get('/posts/{id}',  'Posts@show');
```

### Events

```php
// Fire an event
\Pramnos\Framework\Event::fire('post.created', ['post' => $post]);

// Listen
\Pramnos\Framework\Event::listen('post.created', function (array $payload) {
    // ...
});
```

### Queue

```php
use Pramnos\Queue\QueueManager;

$queue = new QueueManager($db);
$queue->addTask('SendWelcomeEmail', ['user_id' => 42], priority: 5);
```

Process queue: `./{{CLI_NAME}} queue:process`

## Testing conventions

Every test method must have:
- A **doc-block** explaining what is being tested and why (the invariant or edge case).
- **Inline section comments** (`// Arrange`, `// Act`, `// Assert`) to mark the three phases.

```php
/**
 * A published post must appear in the public listing.
 * An unpublished post must not — even if it was just created.
 */
public function testPublishedPostAppearsInListing(): void
{
    // Arrange
    $post = Post::create(['title' => 'Hello', 'status' => 'published']);

    // Act
    $listing = Post::where('status', 'published')->get();

    // Assert
    $this->assertGreaterThan(0, $listing->numRows);
}
```

Integration tests that touch the DB must run against the real Docker databases —
never mock the database layer.

## Available CLI commands

```bash
./{{CLI_NAME}} migrate                 # Run pending migrations
./{{CLI_NAME}} migrate:rollback        # Rollback last batch
./{{CLI_NAME}} migrate:status          # Show migration status table
./{{CLI_NAME}} migrate:reset           # Roll back all migrations
./{{CLI_NAME}} db:seed                 # Run database seeders
./{{CLI_NAME}} scaffold:views          # Publish bundled view templates
./{{CLI_NAME}} create:controller Name  # Scaffold a controller
./{{CLI_NAME}} create:model Name       # Scaffold a model
./{{CLI_NAME}} create:migration Name   # Scaffold a migration
./{{CLI_NAME}} queue:process           # Start queue worker
./{{CLI_NAME}} health:check            # Check system health
```

